710763f-a.text: Twelfth Avenue, north from West 39th Street, showing the Avenue closed to traffic to provide a crossing for the cattle unloading at the rivers edge. 733245f-a.text: Squatters Colony: Shacks of the unemployed on the Hudson River to the north and south of West 39th Street. January 28, 1932. P. L. Sperr.

712600f-a.text: West 39th Street, east from, but not including Twelfth Ave., showing freight yards of the N.Y. Central R.R. on the south side of the street. The rectangular shaped structure shown is the ventilation building for the midtown Lincoln Tunnel, and is on the S.W. corner of Eleventh Ave. March 4, 1937. P. L. Sperr.

712528f-b.text:
View 1: #13 East 39th Street, north side from 38th Street, showing the narrow 12-story house called the Stearling Bronze Building. May 27, 1939.

View 2: East 39th Street, north side looking eastward to First Avenue showing cranes at work on East River Terminal. The Nieto Co. warehouse on the corner of First Avenue. July 23, 1939.

View 3: East 39th Street, south side between First and Second Avenue showing demolition for new road. October 3, 1940.

P. L. Sperr.
